from preventable bugs. The same attack patterns repeat across hundreds of

3
00:00:10,728 --> 00:00:18,529
hacks: reentrancy, missing access control, unchecked external calls, price oracle manipulation.

4
00:00:18,629 --> 00:00:23,769
In this episode, I'll show you the defensive code patterns that

5
00:00:23,869 --> 00:00:29,923
prevent each category of attack. If you're building on-chain or evaluating

6
00:00:30,023 --> 00:00:33,500
protocol security — this is your checklist.

7
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:38,108
Welcome to QuantiFire. We covered the attack vectors in

8
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:42,968
episode 21. Today is the builder's perspective: the design

9
00:00:43,068 --> 00:00:49,253
patterns, code conventions, and architectural decisions that make contracts

10
00:00:49,353 --> 00:00:54,280
resistant to each attack class. These patterns are distilled

11
00:00:54,380 --> 00:00:59,475
from OpenZeppelin, Trail of Bits, ConsenSys Diligence, and the

12
00:00:59,575 --> 00:01:02,660
