13
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:11,298
Pattern one: Checks-Effects-Interactions — the most important pattern in Solidity.

14
00:01:11,398 --> 00:01:17,719
For every state-changing function: first, validate all inputs and preconditions

15
00:01:17,819 --> 00:01:23,571
with require statements. Second, update all state variables. Third, call

16
00:01:23,671 --> 00:01:28,854
external contracts last. The vulnerable pattern on the left sends

17
00:01:28,954 --> 00:01:34,056
ETH before updating the balance — an attacker's receive function

18
00:01:34,156 --> 00:01:39,176
can call withdraw again before the balance is updated, draining

19
00:01:39,276 --> 00:01:43,566
the pool. The correct pattern on the right updates the

20
00:01:43,666 --> 00:01:49,580
balance first, then interacts. The reentrancy attack is impossible because

21
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:54,457
the state is already updated when the external call happens.

22
00:01:54,557 --> 00:02:00,553
Add OpenZeppelin's nonReentrant modifier as belt-and-suspenders protection.

23
00:02:05,066 --> 00:02:10,791
The six non-negotiable security patterns. One: CEI pattern on every

24
00:02:10,891 --> 00:02:19,050
state-changing function. Two: ReentrancyGuard with the nonReentrant modifier from OpenZeppelin.

25
00:02:19,150 --> 00:02:25,396
Three: role-based access control — every sensitive function must restrict

26
00:02:25,496 --> 00:02:32,351
callers explicitly. Never leave admin functions callable by arbitrary addresses.

27
00:02:32,451 --> 00:02:37,045
Four: Chainlink price feed for oracles — never use AMM

28
00:02:37,145 --> 00:02:42,174
spot price as a primary oracle for collateral valuation. It

29
00:02:42,274 --> 00:02:47,738
is manipulatable with flash loans. Five: 48-hour timelock on all

30
00:02:47,838 --> 00:02:53,128
admin operations — this is what prevents governance flash loan

31
00:02:53,228 --> 00:02:58,953
attacks. Six: Solidity 0.8 or higher for automatic integer overflow

32
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:02,865
protection. The cost of an audit is 30 to 100

33
00:03:02,965 --> 00:03:07,907
thousand dollars. The cost of a hack is everything. Always

34
00:03:08,007 --> 00:03:12,862
audit with at least one professional firm before mainnet.

35
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:22,861
Security is architecture, not an afterthought. Build with Checks-Effects-Interactions, ReentrancyGuard,

36
00:03:22,961 --> 00:03:28,470
and AccessControl from the start. Use Chainlink for oracles. Add

37
00:03:28,570 --> 00:03:33,641
timelocks on all admin operations. Then audit with at least

38
00:03:33,741 --> 00:03:39,251
one professional firm before mainnet. Final episode of Series 5:

39
